WEBVTT

00:06.031 --> 00:08.299
BOY:
Come on, boy! Let's go!

00:08.333 --> 00:11.202
WOMAN: All of this property ends
about right there.

00:11.236 --> 00:12.603
WOMAN 2:
Yeah.

00:12.638 --> 00:14.405
Good job! Let's go
throw the ball.

00:14.439 --> 00:17.175
This would be such a great place
to raise a family.

00:17.209 --> 00:18.910
Oh, and the school
district is fantastic.

00:18.944 --> 00:21.779
I wish I could go
to first grade again. (laughs)

00:21.814 --> 00:24.015
I don't know, Peter.
It looks like a swamp.

00:24.049 --> 00:25.364
That's what those
lots looked like, too.

00:25.389 --> 00:27.318
And now, voila!

00:27.319 --> 00:29.554
And it's only a half an hour
from work.

00:29.588 --> 00:31.155
Come on, boy, get it!

00:31.190 --> 00:32.323
I don't want
to twist your arm,

00:32.357 --> 00:34.058
but these lots
are going fast.

00:34.092 --> 00:36.360
We were hoping to find something
to move into soon.

00:36.395 --> 00:37.915
That's the beauty
of Homegrove Estates.

00:37.930 --> 00:40.665
The contractor assures me
they can have your house

00:40.699 --> 00:42.967
up and running
within the year.

00:43.001 --> 00:45.903
Hey, boy.
We can get a dog.

00:45.938 --> 00:47.471
You always wanted
a puppy.

00:47.506 --> 00:49.674
Come here, boy.
A year? Really?

00:49.708 --> 00:50.908
Come here.

00:50.943 --> 00:52.944
And we can
customize everything?

00:52.978 --> 00:54.612
Everything.

00:54.646 --> 00:57.315
This could be our own slice
of heaven, Care-Bear.

00:57.349 --> 00:59.317
No smog,

00:59.351 --> 01:00.518
no crime...

01:05.324 --> 01:06.691
Oh!
Oh, my God!

01:06.725 --> 01:09.093
Let's get out of here.
Let's get out of here!

01:09.127 --> 01:12.296
Wait! No!
I have other available lots!

01:17.402 --> 01:19.704
Okay, we have to get up.

01:19.738 --> 01:21.706
I don't want
to have to fire you

01:21.740 --> 01:22.974
for being late.

01:23.008 --> 01:25.877
I'll appeal
and tell them why.

01:25.911 --> 01:29.280
SAROYAN:
Mm-mm, up, up...

01:29.314 --> 01:30.882
(groans)

01:33.318 --> 01:37.054
(groans)
Not sure I told you...

01:37.089 --> 01:39.223
my parents are coming
to town.

01:39.258 --> 01:41.392
No, you didn't.

01:43.228 --> 01:44.862
That's good.

01:44.897 --> 01:46.498
I mean, you haven't
seen them in a while.

01:46.505 --> 01:47.965
Yeah.

01:47.966 --> 01:50.668
They want to meet you.

01:50.702 --> 01:53.704
Okay, uh, the way you said that
sounds horrifying.

01:53.739 --> 01:55.106
No, no, no.

01:55.140 --> 01:57.642
It'll be fun.
They're gonna love you.

01:57.676 --> 01:58.776
We've been dating long enough

01:58.810 --> 02:00.144
for me to know
when you're lying.

02:00.178 --> 02:02.647
It's just, they're
a little... traditional,

02:02.681 --> 02:05.449
old school, and they still think
of me as their crazy son.

02:05.484 --> 02:06.784
Okay, this is getting worse
and worse.

02:06.818 --> 02:09.287
No, no, no.
Yes. You're saying that, to them,

02:09.321 --> 02:10.588
I'm gonna be
another one of your mistakes?

02:10.622 --> 02:12.256
Why exactly?

02:12.291 --> 02:15.393
Because I'm your non-Iranian,
non-Muslim, black girlfriend?

02:15.427 --> 02:17.728
This came out all wrong.
(text alert sounds)

02:17.763 --> 02:19.864
No, I think it came out
exactly right.

02:21.600 --> 02:23.768
I got a body
in a swamp.

02:23.802 --> 02:26.170
We can talk about this later.

02:30.275 --> 02:33.010
(indistinct radio transmission)

02:35.414 --> 02:37.181
(siren wails briefly)

02:37.215 --> 02:40.418
Based on the vertical nature
of the frontal bone as well

02:40.452 --> 02:42.219
as the mental eminence
of the mandible,

02:42.254 --> 02:44.889
the victim appears to be female,
in her mid-30s.

02:44.923 --> 02:48.159
The prominent nature of the
maxilla suggests Caucasian.

02:48.193 --> 02:49.894
The organs
show no sign

02:49.928 --> 02:52.096
of decomposition despite
the amount of predation

02:52.130 --> 02:53.631
on the rest
of the body.

02:53.665 --> 02:54.999
HODGINS: Someone's getting marked
tardy today.

02:55.033 --> 02:57.034
I called you, and you never
picked up your phone.

02:57.069 --> 02:58.703
Hey, look, there's nothing
I could do, okay?

02:58.737 --> 03:00.705
The assistant director--
he just kept me at the office.

03:00.739 --> 03:02.073
Is everything okay?

03:02.107 --> 03:03.207
Yeah, yeah, just, you know,

03:03.241 --> 03:04.575
reviewing some case files,
that's all.

03:04.609 --> 03:06.777
Case file? Your case files?
Did you make a mistake?

03:06.812 --> 03:07.878
No, not my mistakes, okay?

03:07.913 --> 03:09.847
I was just reviewing
some other reports

03:09.881 --> 03:11.716
for some other agents,
that's all.

03:11.750 --> 03:13.384
Wow, sounds like you're
teacher's pet.

03:13.418 --> 03:15.152
Ha-ha! Okay, enough with
the school references, okay?

03:15.187 --> 03:16.988
What's up with swamp thing?
Not sure.

03:17.022 --> 03:18.422
Animals have eaten
the hands and feet.

03:18.457 --> 03:20.491
Normally, they'd eat
the meaty parts first.

03:20.525 --> 03:22.960
I have a question.
So why is it that, um,

03:22.995 --> 03:24.528
the animals didn't eat
the meaty parts?

03:24.563 --> 03:26.864
BRENNAN: We have no explanation.
It's very frustrating.

03:26.898 --> 03:30.501
Okay. Well, there any clothes
or personal effects?

03:30.535 --> 03:32.737
No. It appears
to be a body dump.

03:32.771 --> 03:33.771
In addition to predation,

03:33.805 --> 03:35.072
there's extensive fracturing
on the bone.

03:35.107 --> 03:36.273
Beaten to death?

03:36.308 --> 03:37.875
I don't have an explanation
for the fracturing

03:37.909 --> 03:40.111
at this point, but it doesn't
appear to be blunt force.

03:40.145 --> 03:42.046
So, do we at least have
time of death?

03:42.080 --> 03:44.115
HODGINS: Well, that's where it starts
to really get weird.

03:44.149 --> 03:45.716
Insect activity is
all over the place.

03:45.751 --> 03:48.619
We've got colonization
and development of <i>Piophilidae</i>

03:48.653 --> 03:50.287
in the skull and extremities.

03:50.322 --> 03:52.923
That puts time of death between
72 and 96 hours.

03:52.958 --> 03:55.259
So three or four days.
What's so weird about that?

03:55.293 --> 03:56.560
Because in the body cavity,
there's

03:56.595 --> 03:57.561
<i>Calliphoridae</i> larvae,
which indicates

03:57.596 --> 03:59.630
time of death
in the last three hours.

03:59.664 --> 04:01.304
Whoa! The body was found
long before that.

04:01.348 --> 04:02.600
Exactly.

04:02.601 --> 04:05.636
Which accounts for the
<i>Chrysomyarufifacies</i> in the feet,

04:05.670 --> 04:09.340
which puts time of death in
the last 14 days.

04:09.374 --> 04:13.010
Three hours, three days,
two weeks, right? What is it?

04:13.045 --> 04:14.278
Well, evidence says all three.

04:14.312 --> 04:16.514
That's not possible.

