04:36.004 --> 04:51.306
♪

04:53.848 --> 04:56.883
So you have no idea
when she was killed?

04:56.918 --> 04:58.485
None at all.
We're looking for clues

04:58.519 --> 05:00.887
that can narrow it down.

05:00.922 --> 05:03.056
There's something lodged

05:03.091 --> 05:06.762
between the left maxillary
lateral incisor and the canine.

05:06.763 --> 05:08.183
I'm not sure how much
I'm gonna find.

05:08.184 --> 05:10.011
The swamp could have
swallowed up a lot of stuff.

05:10.012 --> 05:11.286
How long will
it take you

05:11.287 --> 05:13.532
to clean and reassemble
the skull, Mr. Vaziri?

05:13.533 --> 05:15.394
We need Angela to do
the reconstruction

05:15.419 --> 05:16.269
as soon as possible.

05:16.270 --> 05:17.938
You're still picking tissue
off the parietal.

05:17.972 --> 05:19.740
Don't you want
to finish that first?

05:19.774 --> 05:21.575
Oh, it's all yours, Mr. Vaziri.

05:21.609 --> 05:27.381
Is it me, or did it just get
totally awkward in here?

05:27.415 --> 05:29.683
It's probably the perplexing
nature of the remains.

05:29.717 --> 05:32.185
Uh, no. Actually, I think
it was the "Mr. Vaziri."

05:32.220 --> 05:34.755
What's going on here?
A murder case.

05:34.789 --> 05:36.323
So if we could focus on
the task at hand...

05:36.357 --> 05:38.258
The skull is
all yours, Mr....

05:38.292 --> 05:39.960
Arastoo.

05:39.994 --> 05:41.395
Thank you.

05:41.429 --> 05:43.563
Is something happening
that I don't understand?

05:43.598 --> 05:44.364
Yes.

05:44.399 --> 05:46.099
This is very odd.

05:46.134 --> 05:47.901
This tissue isn't
from the victim.

05:47.935 --> 05:50.015
It must have mixed in with
hers during decomposition.

05:50.037 --> 05:51.738
It could be evidence
of the assailant.

05:51.773 --> 05:53.373
Or a second victim.

05:53.408 --> 05:56.143
I'll run DNA and a tox screen
and see what I can find.

05:56.177 --> 05:59.346
Oh, Mr. Vaziri, bring up
the X rays of this area

05:59.380 --> 06:01.181
and tell me what you see.

06:05.753 --> 06:08.588
There appears to be
a remodeled injury

06:08.623 --> 06:11.091
to the right posterior
superior iliac crest.

06:11.125 --> 06:13.794
From a large-bore needle?
Yes.

06:13.828 --> 06:16.296
We can identify the victim
without a reconstruction.

06:16.330 --> 06:18.198
The victim had
a bone marrow aspiration

06:18.232 --> 06:20.100
approximately one year ago.

06:20.134 --> 06:22.702
Then I'll call the National
Bone Marrow Registry.

06:26.374 --> 06:28.909
Whew! So, the victim's name
is Madeline Papadelis.

06:28.943 --> 06:31.144
She'd been off the grid
for four months;

06:31.179 --> 06:32.946
no credit card information,
no cell phone information.

06:32.980 --> 06:34.381
No missing persons
report filed,

06:34.415 --> 06:36.650
no immediate family.
Do you have anything on her?

06:36.684 --> 06:38.485
Angela's sending over
more stuff.

06:38.519 --> 06:40.287
Whoa! Wait a second.
That more?

06:40.321 --> 06:42.122
Yes, sir.
SWEETS: This all about the victim?

06:42.156 --> 06:43.957
No, all of that is from
the assistant director.

06:43.991 --> 06:46.126
It's different.
He said no rush. If you could review 'em

06:46.160 --> 06:48.395
by the end of the week,
it should be fine.

06:48.429 --> 06:49.696
No rush?
There's over 50 cases here!

06:49.730 --> 06:51.331
I'm in the middle
of a murder investigation here.

06:51.365 --> 06:53.233
This has nothing
to do with me, sir.

06:53.267 --> 06:54.734
Oh, please,
you gotta be kidding me.

06:54.769 --> 06:56.603
I'm just delivering what I was told.
Right, okay.

06:56.637 --> 06:59.673
So, the assistant director's
having you review

06:59.707 --> 07:01.675
other agents' files?
That's-that's a big deal, Booth.

07:01.709 --> 07:04.044
It won't be if the person
who killed Madeline gets away.

07:04.078 --> 07:05.879
They don't ask just anyone to do that.
You know what?

07:05.913 --> 07:06.980
They're probably short-staffed.
They just want me

07:07.014 --> 07:08.482
to do double duty.
Uh, they could be

07:08.516 --> 07:10.183
looking at you for a promotion.
I tell you what.

07:10.218 --> 07:12.786
Why don't you just help me
with Madeline's case, all right?

07:12.820 --> 07:14.855
You have noticed I'm up
to my ears here in stuff.

07:14.889 --> 07:16.122
Sure.
Right, okay.

07:16.157 --> 07:17.457
So this is everything
that Angela

07:17.492 --> 07:19.259
has uncovered so far
about the case.

07:19.293 --> 07:21.761
She divorced, so any contact
with the ex-husband?

07:21.796 --> 07:23.890
Haven't located him yet.
Look at this.

07:23.915 --> 07:24.397
Hmm?

07:24.398 --> 07:28.201
What is this,
a tribute site to her kid?

07:28.236 --> 07:30.370
Yeah, her kid had
cystic fibrosis.

07:30.404 --> 07:32.739
She was only six years old.
She died 13 months ago.

07:32.773 --> 07:34.674
A lot of people give up
after something like that.

07:34.709 --> 07:35.909
They turn to drugs,

07:35.943 --> 07:37.777
anything to help them forget
about the pain.

07:37.812 --> 07:40.447
It's interesting that she
didn't have any clothes on.

07:40.481 --> 07:42.616
You're thinking
sexual assault?

07:42.650 --> 07:44.985
Or a sexual situation
that got out of hand.

07:45.019 --> 07:47.053
You know, sex can be used
as a way

07:47.088 --> 07:49.256
to numb yourself
from the pain, so...

07:49.290 --> 07:51.091
I got a text here. Oh.
What?

07:51.125 --> 07:53.193
Madeline took out a restraining
order on her ex-husband

07:53.227 --> 07:56.930
a year and a half ago.
He threatened to kill her.

07:59.767 --> 08:02.569
Hey, have you found a way
to determine time of death?

08:02.603 --> 08:05.305
No. It still technically
appears as if different parts

08:05.339 --> 08:07.107
of the body died
at different times.

08:07.141 --> 08:08.675
You?
Insect activity's telling me

08:08.709 --> 08:11.411
the same thing. I moved on
so I wouldn't feel stupid.

08:11.445 --> 08:13.580
So the fiber Dr. Brennan
found lodged

08:13.614 --> 08:15.515
in the victim's teeth
turned out to be chloroform.

08:15.550 --> 08:16.750
If the killer drugged

08:16.784 --> 08:18.151
Madeline before he killed her,

08:18.185 --> 08:19.920
maybe we're dealing
with a kidnapping.

08:19.954 --> 08:22.856
Could be. There were some
fibers found on her back

08:22.890 --> 08:24.724
made from silk and
cuprammonium rayon.

08:24.759 --> 08:26.927
The blend is used in WorldCore
sleeping bags.

08:26.961 --> 08:28.161
Drugged and zipped up

08:28.195 --> 08:30.463
in a sleeping bag.
It would explain

08:30.498 --> 08:32.032
being missing
for four months.

08:32.066 --> 08:34.100
Hey, I hear Arastoo's parents
are coming for a visit.

08:34.135 --> 08:36.001
Yeah. He hasn't seen them
in a long time.

08:36.037 --> 08:37.270
You gonna meet them?

08:37.304 --> 08:40.073
Haven't decided yet.
I don't want to intrude.

08:40.107 --> 08:41.408
He hasn't asked?

08:41.442 --> 08:43.208
No, he's asked.

08:43.244 --> 08:45.011
Oh, it's too loaded:
conflicting loyalties,

08:45.046 --> 08:46.246
you're not sure how

08:46.280 --> 08:47.847
that will play out.
I get it.

08:47.882 --> 08:50.283
It's not that big a deal, really.
That's what I said

08:50.318 --> 08:52.786
until Angela's father
knocked me out and tattooed me.

08:52.820 --> 08:54.688
Is that supposed
to be helping me?

08:54.722 --> 08:56.356
(computer trills)

08:56.390 --> 08:58.491
What's that?

08:58.526 --> 09:00.460
The DNA results
from the foreign tissue

09:00.494 --> 09:02.662
I found
on the victim.

09:05.099 --> 09:06.633
It's part of a tongue.

09:06.667 --> 09:08.535
A tongue?
That is creepy.

09:08.569 --> 09:11.838
A fox tongue, apparently.
And these samples appear

09:11.872 --> 09:13.340
to be from other
small scavengers.

09:13.374 --> 09:15.575
All somehow stuck to the victim.

09:15.610 --> 09:18.445
Maybe it was
a ritualistic killing.

09:18.479 --> 09:21.414
So, the ex-husband, he lives
in a cabin outside the city.

09:21.449 --> 09:23.116
Another agent's
bringing him in.

09:23.150 --> 09:24.684
Because you're still working
on other agents' cases?

09:24.719 --> 09:26.319
Look, every time I say no,

09:26.354 --> 09:28.388
the assistant director says
he can't get along without me.

09:28.422 --> 09:30.991
I feel the same way.

09:31.025 --> 09:33.460
What if they promote you
to a desk job?

09:33.494 --> 09:35.695
Are they gonna give me
another partner?

09:35.730 --> 09:38.264
Look, I am not gonna be
promoted to a desk job, okay?

09:38.299 --> 09:40.567
Plus, you're not gonna get
a new partner.

09:40.601 --> 09:41.935
They're not gonna promote you

09:41.969 --> 09:43.803
and leave you
in the same position.

09:43.838 --> 09:45.472
Look, everyone is just getting
way ahead

09:45.506 --> 09:46.806
of themselves right now,
all right?

09:46.841 --> 09:48.541
I'm just doing
this guy a favor.

09:48.576 --> 09:52.646
(phone rings) Just figuring out,
looking at ex-cases. Booth.

09:52.680 --> 09:54.681
Yeah, great. On our way.

09:54.715 --> 09:56.650
Bringing in the ex-husband.
Come with me?

09:56.684 --> 09:58.184
Why?
Why?

09:58.219 --> 10:00.387
Because you're my partner.
(clicks tongue)

10:01.756 --> 10:04.424
I can't believe Madeline's dead.

10:04.458 --> 10:06.259
Oy, save the tears, okay?

10:06.293 --> 10:08.828
You haven't contacted your ex
in over, what, four months?

10:08.863 --> 10:10.630
Because she had
a restraining order against me.

10:10.665 --> 10:12.132
Because you tried to kill her.

10:12.166 --> 10:13.867
No, that is not true.
We fought,

10:13.901 --> 10:15.769
I was cleaning my rifle
and I waved it around.

10:15.803 --> 10:17.470
What were you fighting about?

10:17.505 --> 10:19.339
Same thing we always
fought about--

10:19.373 --> 10:22.242
our little girl, Karine.

10:22.276 --> 10:24.611
Madeline wanted
to put her through

10:24.645 --> 10:26.212
all these god-awful
treatments.

10:26.247 --> 10:29.215
And since she had full custody,
I couldn't do anything about it.

10:29.250 --> 10:30.250
Must've been angry, huh?

10:30.284 --> 10:31.685
Yeah, wouldn't you be?

10:31.719 --> 10:36.122
She was torturing my daughter,
even-even after the doctors said

10:36.157 --> 10:38.458
she'd never get any better.

10:38.492 --> 10:40.360
You're a hunter,
aren't you, Mr. Papadelis?

10:40.394 --> 10:42.028
That illegal?
We found the tongues

10:42.063 --> 10:45.231
and snouts of small animals
on your ex-wife's remains.

10:45.266 --> 10:47.133
So you think...?

10:48.302 --> 10:49.869
You're crazy!

10:49.904 --> 10:51.304
Maybe you tortured
your ex

10:51.338 --> 10:53.106
the way you thought she tortured
your daughter.

10:53.140 --> 10:55.442
No.
If you're innocent,

10:55.476 --> 10:57.110
I'm sure you'd be happy
to let us examine

10:57.144 --> 10:58.578
your camping equipment and guns.

10:58.612 --> 10:59.646
I'm a member of the NRA.

10:59.680 --> 11:01.514
I know my rights.

11:01.549 --> 11:03.750
You need a warrant.
Oh, right.

11:03.784 --> 11:05.452
That's right, a warrant.
Like this one here?

11:05.486 --> 11:06.786
Here you go. Look at that.

11:06.821 --> 11:08.722
That okay for you,
Mr. Huntsman?

11:14.363 --> 11:17.826
Hey.
Okay, initially I thought

11:17.827 --> 11:20.028
the damage to the organs
was caused by predation,

11:20.063 --> 11:21.930
animals tearing them apart.

11:21.965 --> 11:23.866
But these are
actually fractures.

11:23.900 --> 11:25.940
All right, I'm not Dr. B,
but organs don't fracture.

11:25.969 --> 11:27.002
Only bones do.

11:27.036 --> 11:28.303
Unless the organs were frozen.

11:28.338 --> 11:30.372
I also found urine
in the bladder,

11:30.406 --> 11:31.807
which a normal body would expel.

11:31.841 --> 11:33.675
Unless it was frozen
very soon after death.

11:33.710 --> 11:35.010
Freezing.

11:35.044 --> 11:36.912
Freezing would account
for the various insect

11:36.946 --> 11:39.014
and larval stages I found.

11:39.048 --> 11:40.315
And would explain
why the animals didn't feed

11:40.350 --> 11:41.617
on the torso and organs first.

11:41.651 --> 11:43.152
Yeah, they were
the last to thaw.

11:43.186 --> 11:44.653
Which also explains the tongues

11:44.687 --> 11:45.888
and tissue from the scavengers.

11:45.922 --> 11:47.156
If they tried to feed

11:47.190 --> 11:48.323
on the organs when
they were frozen,

11:48.358 --> 11:49.825
their tongues would stick.
Yeah.

11:49.859 --> 11:50.859
And would tear off
as they were pulling away.

11:50.894 --> 11:51.994
Wow, so what?

11:52.028 --> 11:53.128
Someone had her locked
in a freezer

11:53.163 --> 11:54.296
for the past four months?

11:54.330 --> 11:55.998
Well, that would be
the easy answer.

11:56.032 --> 11:58.033
I've worked a lot of mob hits,
and they love to freeze.

11:58.067 --> 11:59.902
But I've never seen a freezer

11:59.936 --> 12:02.638
cold enough to fracture a liver.

12:04.307 --> 12:06.909
BOOTH:
<i>Frozen?</i>

12:06.943 --> 12:09.068
It appears that way, although
I haven't found any evidence

12:09.069 --> 12:09.546
Whoa.

12:09.547 --> 12:13.382
of microstructural changes
caused by liquid expansion.

12:13.416 --> 12:15.350
That usually
accompanies freezing,

12:15.385 --> 12:17.152
which is why I'm doing a
histological study of the bones.

12:17.187 --> 12:18.353
Well, psych profiles

12:18.388 --> 12:20.322
of killers that
freeze their victims

12:20.356 --> 12:22.024
kind of go all over the place.

12:22.058 --> 12:23.358
I mean, the killer could
have frozen the victim

12:23.393 --> 12:24.860
to obscure time of death.

12:24.894 --> 12:26.061
So, that's
what happened here, isn't it?

12:26.095 --> 12:27.663
Or the killer

12:27.697 --> 12:29.665
could've put the body
on ice until they found

12:29.699 --> 12:31.366
a more convenient time
to dispose of it.

12:31.401 --> 12:32.834
Or both.
That's a very good point.

12:32.869 --> 12:33.936
That's why the assistant
director asked

12:33.970 --> 12:35.237
for your advice. And mine.

12:35.271 --> 12:37.139
If Sweets is going
over cases, too,

12:37.173 --> 12:39.641
perhaps it's not
about a promotion.

12:39.676 --> 12:41.310
I'm gonna pretend
that wasn't insulting.

12:41.344 --> 12:43.679
So, the assistant director
asked me to review

12:43.713 --> 12:45.214
your test results

12:45.248 --> 12:47.216
and your latest psych profile.
What?

12:47.250 --> 12:48.717
He wants me to
make an analysis

12:48.751 --> 12:50.052
of your performance
and capabilities.

12:50.086 --> 12:51.320
And you're allowed
to tell me that?

12:51.354 --> 12:53.222
Nobody said it
was confidential.

12:53.256 --> 12:54.189
Well, what else do you know?

12:54.224 --> 12:55.524
Um, nothing official yet.

12:55.558 --> 12:56.658
But I heard
that they're staffing

12:56.693 --> 12:58.794
a new field office in Germany.

12:58.828 --> 13:00.462
They need someone to run it.
Germany?

13:00.496 --> 13:01.730
The FBI is a domestic agency.

13:01.764 --> 13:03.398
BOOTH:
Well, not exclusively.

13:03.433 --> 13:05.267
I mean, when there are suspected
terrorists or attacks

13:05.301 --> 13:08.604
against embassies or consulates,
the FBI always responds.

13:08.638 --> 13:09.838
That's more

13:09.872 --> 13:10.906
than a regular promotion, Booth.

13:10.940 --> 13:13.075
That sounds like a big honor.

13:13.109 --> 13:14.710
Well, how long
would the tour be?

13:14.744 --> 13:15.877
I heard two years.
I'm not leaving you

13:15.912 --> 13:17.980
and Christine,
so it's not gonna happen.

13:18.014 --> 13:19.581
You've clearly excelled
at your job, Booth.

13:19.616 --> 13:21.483
You should allow yourself
to be recognized in that way.

13:21.517 --> 13:23.785
Oh, I-I have to get
back to the lab.

13:23.820 --> 13:25.153
Uh, we can talk
about this later.

13:25.188 --> 13:27.589
There's nothing to talk about.

13:27.624 --> 13:29.358
You sound defensive, Booth.
I'm not defensive.

13:29.392 --> 13:30.759
I'm starting
to get annoyed, okay?

13:30.793 --> 13:32.354
People are way ahead
of themselves here.

13:32.362 --> 13:34.830
Okay.

13:36.733 --> 13:39.301
Booth got Madeline's
credit card records.

13:39.335 --> 13:41.436
She spent practically nothing.

13:41.471 --> 13:45.340
The one consistent charge were
her bus passes from the MTA.

13:45.375 --> 13:46.908
She got the last one
five months ago.

13:46.943 --> 13:49.077
Just before she disappeared.

13:49.112 --> 13:52.247
The first purchase was made
just after her daughter died.

13:52.282 --> 13:54.349
She only used them on
Saturdays when she took

13:54.384 --> 13:55.951
the round trip
to Vienna, Virginia.

13:55.985 --> 13:57.519
Looks like her last trip
was four months ago

13:57.553 --> 13:59.187
when she disappeared.

13:59.222 --> 14:01.490
Yeah, and there was no
return ride for that trip.

14:01.524 --> 14:03.692
Huh. Well...

14:03.726 --> 14:05.961
we still haven't ruled out
sexual assault, you know.

14:05.995 --> 14:07.963
I mean, Sweets says
some grieving victims

14:07.997 --> 14:09.631
turn to sex
to dull the pain.

14:09.666 --> 14:12.434
So, you think she was going
up there to meet someone?

14:12.468 --> 14:15.137
Maybe, and maybe that person
got a little too kinky,

14:15.171 --> 14:17.973
and chloroformed
and abducted her.

